name: superoxide dismutase
classes: Acting on superoxide as acceptor (only sub-subclass identified to date)
comment: A metalloprotein; also known as erythrocuprein, hemocuprein or cytocuprein. Enzymes from most eukaryotes contain both copper and zinc; those from mitochondria and most prokaryotes contain manganese or iron.
